                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                                <seg type="script">Written in a mediocre handwriting.</seg>
                                <date/>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <list>
                                <item xml:id="a1">
                                    <desc type="OwnershipNote"/>
                                    <locus target="#34"/>
                                    <q xml:lang="gez">ዝ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘወልደ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ዘአጥረዮ፡ በንዋዮ፡ ወካልዕ፡ ስሙ፡ ዘዓጀር፡ ወአቡሁ፡ ተክለ፡ አብ፡ ወካልዕ፡ ስሙ፡ ወርቁ፡ ወእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ሩፋኤል፡ ወካልዕ፡ ስማ፡ 
                                        <choice>
                                 <sic resp="PRS3562Dillmann">ወይዘኖ፡</sic>
                                 <corr resp="MV">ወይዘሮ፡</corr>
                              </choice> ዘገች፡ ትውልደ፡ ከፄ፡ ፋሲል፡ ቤት፡ ነው።
                                    </q>
                                    <q xml:lang="en">"This book belongs to Walda Gabrǝʾel, who bought it with his own money and is also called Za-ʿAǧǧar. His father is Takla 
                                        ʾAb and is also called Warqu; his mother is Walatta Rufāʾel and is also called lady Zagačč, from the house of ʾaṣe Fasil"</q>
                                    <desc>
                                        The note states that the owner of the book is <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11103WaldaG">Walda Gabrǝʾel</persName>, also called  Za-ʿAǧǧar. 
                                        The note also mentions his father <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11104TaklaAb">Takla ʾAb</persName>, also called Warqu, and his mother 
                                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11105WalattaR">Walatta Rufāʾel</persName>, also called lady Zagačč. 
                                        She is said to belong to the house of king <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4015Fasilada">Fasil</persName>.                                        
                                    </desc>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                        </additions>
